      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vector 1: Log Leakage"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Logging is the most common leakage vector. Developers add verbose logging during development; production deployments inherit those logs. The fix is to log a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "sanitised",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " form of the conversation, never the raw text."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import re, hashlib\n\n_PII_REDACT = re.compile(\n    r\"(\\b\\d{3}-\\d{2}-\\d{4}\\b\"                                     # SSN\n    r\"|\\b[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\\.[A-Z|a-z]{2,}\\b\"       # email\n    r\"|\\b(?:\\+?1[-\\s.]?)?\\(?\\d{3}\\)?[-\\s.]\\d{3}[-\\s.]\\d{4}\\b\"  # US phone\n    r\"|\\b(?:4[0-9]{12}(?:[0-9]{3})?)\\b)\"                              # Visa card\n)\n\ndef redact_for_log(text: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Replace PII in any string before it reaches a log sink.\"\"\"\n    return _PII_REDACT.sub(\"[REDACTED]\", text)\n\ndef log_conversation_turn(\n    session_id: str,\n    role: str,\n    content: str,\n    logger,\n) -> None:\n    safe_content = redact_for_log(content)\n    # Also truncate long messages to prevent token-level leaks in log aggregators\n    if len(safe_content) > 500:\n        safe_content = safe_content[:500] + \"\u2026[truncated]\"\n    logger.info({\n        \"event\": \"conversation_turn\",\n        \"session_id\": hashlib.sha256(session_id.encode()).hexdigest()[:12],  # pseudonymise session\n        \"role\": role,\n        \"content\": safe_content,\n    })"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vector 2: Error Message Leakage"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When an LLM call fails, naive error handlers may include the prompt in the exception. An exception propagated to the user or to a shared error tracker (Sentry, Datadog) can expose the full conversation context."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import traceback, logging\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\nclass SafeModelError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Public-facing error that never contains context window content.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, public_message: str, *, internal_ref: str):\n        super().__init__(public_message)\n        self.internal_ref = internal_ref\n\ndef call_model_safely(prompt: str, model_fn) -> str:\n    try:\n        return model_fn(prompt)\n    except Exception as exc:\n        # Log the full exception internally with the prompt REDACTED\n        ref = hashlib.sha256(traceback.format_exc().encode()).hexdigest()[:8]\n        logger.error(\n            \"Model call failed [ref=%s]: %s\",\n            ref,\n            redact_for_log(str(exc)),\n            exc_info=False,   # don't include the stack trace in the log message\n        )\n        # Raise a safe error without the prompt or stack trace\n        raise SafeModelError(\n            \"The request could not be completed. Please try again.\",\n            internal_ref=ref,\n        ) from None"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vector 3: Model Memory and Fine-Tuning Leakage"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Language models can memorise verbatim fragments of their training data, particularly for repeated or unique sequences. If a fine-tuning dataset includes PII \u2014 even in support transcripts that \"anonymised\" customer names but left account numbers \u2014 the fine-tuned model may reproduce those sequences when prompted appropriately."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Differential privacy training:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " adds calibrated noise during gradient computation (DP-SGD). This provides a formal privacy guarantee but degrades model utility \u2014 accept only models with epsilon <= 8 for high-sensitivity data."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Dataset scrubbing before fine-tuning:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " apply the same PII detection and redaction pipeline to the training corpus before the fine-tuning run. This is mandatory, not optional."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Memorisation probing:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " after fine-tuning, run a canary extraction test: embed known fake PII strings in the training data and probe the model to see if it reproduces them. If canaries are reproduced, abort the deployment."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import secrets\n\ndef generate_canary(label: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Creates a fake SSN-shaped canary with a known label for extraction testing.\"\"\"\n    rand = secrets.randbelow(999999)\n    return f\"CANARY-{label}: {rand // 1000:03d}-{rand % 1000 // 100:02d}-{rand % 100:04d}\"\n\ndef probe_for_canary(model_fn, canary_prefix: str, prompts: list[str]) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns True if the model reproduces the canary in any probe response.\n    A True result means the model has memorised training data \u2014 do not deploy.\n    \"\"\"\n    for prompt in prompts:\n        response = model_fn(prompt)\n        if canary_prefix in response:\n            return True\n    return False"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vector 4: Cross-User Context Leakage"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multi-tenant agent deployments must ensure that cached state from one user's session is never accessible to another. The most common mistake is using a shared LRU cache that is keyed on content hash rather than "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "(user_id, content_hash)",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from functools import lru_cache\nfrom typing import Callable, TypeVar\n\nT = TypeVar(\"T\")\n\nclass UserScopedCache:\n    \"\"\"\n    Wraps any callable to add user-scoped caching.\n    Cache keys are always (user_id, *args) \u2014 never shared across users.\n    \"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, fn: Callable, maxsize: int = 128):\n        self._fn = fn\n        self._cache: dict[tuple, object] = {}\n        self._maxsize = maxsize\n\n    def __call__(self, user_id: str, *args):\n        key = (user_id, *args)\n        if key not in self._cache:\n            if len(self._cache) >= self._maxsize:\n                # Evict oldest entry (FIFO approximation)\n                oldest = next(iter(self._cache))\n                del self._cache[oldest]\n            self._cache[key] = self._fn(*args)\n        return self._cache[key]\n\n    def invalidate_user(self, user_id: str) -> int:\n        keys_to_delete = [k for k in self._cache if k[0] == user_id]\n        for k in keys_to_delete:\n            del self._cache[k]\n        return len(keys_to_delete)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vector 5: Sub-Agent Context Overshare"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When an orchestrator spawns a sub-agent, it must pass only the context that sub-agent genuinely needs \u2014 not the full system prompt (which may contain credentials or internal policies) and not the full conversation history (which may contain other users' PII from earlier turns)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\n\n@dataclass\nclass SubAgentContext:\n    task_description: str\n    relevant_data: dict[str, str]   # only the fields this sub-agent needs\n    allowed_tools: list[str]        # explicit allowlist, not inherited from parent\n    # NOT included: full system prompt, parent session history,\n    # credentials, other-user data, internal configurations\n\ndef build_sub_agent_context(\n    task: str,\n    parent_context: dict,\n    sub_agent_allowed_fields: set[str],\n    sub_agent_tools: list[str],\n) -> SubAgentContext:\n    \"\"\"\n    Filter parent context down to only the fields the sub-agent needs.\n    Raises if requested fields are not in the safe list.\n    \"\"\"\n    SENSITIVE_PARENT_FIELDS = {\"system_prompt\", \"api_key\", \"db_password\", \"all_user_history\"}\n    requested = sub_agent_allowed_fields & set(parent_context.keys())\n    leaked = requested & SENSITIVE_PARENT_FIELDS\n    if leaked:\n        raise PermissionError(f\"Sub-agent context would expose sensitive fields: {leaked}\")\n    return SubAgentContext(\n        task_description=task,\n        relevant_data={k: parent_context[k] for k in requested},\n        allowed_tools=sub_agent_tools,\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Vector 6: Vector Store Contamination"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A retrieval-augmented agent stores embeddings of documents or conversation chunks in a vector store. If those chunks contain PII and the store is shared across users, a similarity search triggered by any user can surface another user's personal data."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n\n@dataclass\nclass EmbeddingRecord:\n    chunk_id: str\n    owner_user_id: str      # always set; used for access control on retrieval\n    text: str               # already redacted \u2014 PII-clean before embedding\n    embedding: list[float]\n    sensitivity_label: str  # \"PUBLIC\" | \"USER_PRIVATE\" | \"INTERNAL\"\n\nclass UserScopedVectorStore:\n    def __init__(self, backend):\n        self._backend = backend\n\n    def upsert(self, record: EmbeddingRecord) -> None:\n        # Store the sensitivity label and owner alongside the embedding\n        self._backend.upsert(\n            id=record.chunk_id,\n            vector=record.embedding,\n            metadata={\n                \"owner_user_id\": record.owner_user_id,\n                \"sensitivity_label\": record.sensitivity_label,\n                \"text\": record.text,  # already PII-clean\n            },\n        )\n\n    def search(\n        self,\n        query_embedding: list[float],\n        requesting_user_id: str,\n        top_k: int = 5,\n    ) -> list[dict]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Always filter by owner_user_id == requesting_user_id\n        OR sensitivity_label == \"PUBLIC\".\n        Never return USER_PRIVATE records to a different user.\n        \"\"\"\n        results = self._backend.search(\n            vector=query_embedding,\n            top_k=top_k * 5,  # over-fetch then filter\n            filter={\n                \"or\": [\n                    {\"owner_user_id\": {\"eq\": requesting_user_id}},\n                    {\"sensitivity_label\": {\"eq\": \"PUBLIC\"}},\n                ]\n            },\n        )\n        return results[:top_k]"
          }
        ]
      },
