            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Data leakage in agentic systems is largely unintentional \u2014 it arises from verbose logging, exception handling that includes context, shared caches without user-scoped keys, over-broad sub-agent context, and vector stores that lack retrieval-time access control. Six vectors require dedicated mitigations: "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "log sanitisation",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (redact PII before any write to a log sink), "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "safe error handling",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (raise opaque public errors that contain no context), "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "fine-tuning hygiene",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (scrub PII from training data and probe for canary memorisation), "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "user-scoped caching",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (cache keys must include user_id), "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "sub-agent context minimisation",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (pass only the fields the sub-agent needs), and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "vector store access control",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (filter every retrieval to owner_user_id or PUBLIC). An operational checklist run after each release catches regressions before they affect users."
          }
        ]
